\fs26 active keys\
\
space\
escape\
enter\
return\
command\
control\
shift\
left and right arrow\
up and down arrow\
r f g v c e m 0\
delete\
\
\
spacebar - if you just muted or unmuted a track on the upper half of the monome the space bar will select that track if you just hit a pad on the lower half to make a sound hitting the space bar will take you into big pad mode.\
\
return - this will start and stop playback\
enter - if you have a full keyboard this will bring up the last pad you touched for editing.  the v key also does this.\
\
escape - this serves a variety of purposes:  all notes off, cancel duplicate, cancel clear track.\
\
up and down arrow keys - these will navigate you through pages.  if you select some other number box, they will increment or decrement that box until you  click out side of it.\
\
left and right arrow keys - (only active on the 64 and 128) these will let you access the first or second set of pads and tracks.  \
\
control, shift and command keys - these will help you quickly manipulate waveforms in the waveform window.  command + drag will zoom in and out. shift and drag adjusts a previous selection, control and drag will move the current selection and resize it based on mouse height.\
\
r - this will start recording for the currently selected track\
f - this will play the currently active voice\
g - this will play the currently active pad\
v - this will play and bring up the last touched pad for editing
\fs24 \
c - this will clear the active track of data if hit twice\
e - this will erase any pad activity in the currently selected track if held down with the pad intended to be removed\
m - this will toggle the mute of the currently selected track\
0 - this will open the options window.\
delete - will tap the tempo\

\fs26 *experimental*\
d - duplicates a pad\
t - copies all the data in a track
